The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Sept. 2: The rate of inflation fell for the fifth consecutive week to 3.08 per cent in the week ended August 20 from 3.13 per cent in the previous week, mainly due to cheaper non-food items and some edible oils. The point-to-point wholesale price index (WPI) based inflation fell by 0.05 per cent during the week. It was 8.46 per cent in the corresponding period last year. The WPI was up 0.1 per cent to 194.3 points. 

 New York, Sept. 2: Machinists at Boeing Co went on Friday for the first time in 10 years, after voting to reject the aircraft maker?s latest contract offer. With 86 per cent of the 18,500 machinists voting for a strike, pickets were put in place at Boeing?s factories in the Washington state.

 New Delhi, Sept. 2: The Indian Commercial Pilots Association today said it is contemplating challenging the directive of the directorate general of civil aviation making it mandatory for pilots to give a six-month notice as it ?violated? not only the labour laws but those governing contracts too.

 Mumbai, Sept. 2: Binani Industries today said it would divest 25 per cent of its stake in subsidiary Binani Cement Ltd to an international investor.

 Mumbai, Sept. 2: Reliance Industries has raised polymer prices across the board following the rise in the international rates of naphtha and crude oil.




